{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Only files changed in the pull request are analyzed — unchanged files are not scanned.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Real failure is at a module handoff: changed-file discovery feeds the scan scheduler. A unit test of only the filter function can miss wiring bugs (wrong path normalization, missed diff entries, or accidental full-repo fallback). Integration is sufficient because behavior text does not require real OS/network/subprocess; GitHub API can be stubbed and filesystem can be local fixtures. Rejected higher levels: System is disqualified by behavior scope (selection logic, not real network/OS timing), Agentic/Workflow are disqualified because no AI/ML decisions are involved.","test_description":"Wire diff-file provider + analysis dispatcher + scanner with fixture repo data; provide a mixed set of changed and unchanged files; assert only changed paths are dispatched/scanned and unchanged paths never appear in scan calls or findings.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.34,"Integration":0.58,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Findings are grouped by severity (error, warning, info) in the posted PR comment.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is between analyzer output, grouping/formatting, and comment payload construction. Unit tests on grouping alone can miss schema/field-name mismatches before posting. Integration is enough because correctness here is deterministic and can be validated with a fake PR-comment client; no real HTTP or model output is required. Rejected higher levels: System is disqualified since real GitHub API behavior is not needed to verify grouping semantics; Agentic/Workflow are disqualified (no LLM/ML dependency).","test_description":"Run analyzer-result objects through the real grouping + comment-render pipeline with a mocked comment sink; assert rendered comment contains three correctly grouped sections and each finding appears under its severity.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.4,"Integration":0.54,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"A pull request that touches 200 files completes analysis within the 10-minute Actions timeout.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"This is explicitly a real runtime/timeout SLO in GitHub Actions. Real failure depends on subprocess performance, filesystem I/O, and wall-clock behavior under CI constraints; in-process fakes can hide it. Integration brake check: (a) yes, real OS/subprocess/timing needed -> System; (b) no AI/ML output dependency; (c) no multi-agentic chain. Rejected higher levels: Agentic/Workflow disqualified by non-LLM behavior text.","test_description":"Execute the lint step end-to-end as a CI-like job against a synthetic PR-sized workspace (200 files) using the real linter subprocess and timing budget assertions; fail if total runtime exceeds a conservative threshold below 10 minutes.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.12,"System":0.86,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"When the linter process crashes on a malformed file, the remaining files are still analyzed and results posted.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Behavior explicitly names a process crash, which is a real subprocess failure mode (exit signal/abrupt termination) that mocks often do not reproduce faithfully. Need to verify supervisor/error-isolation behavior across process boundaries and continuation on remaining files. Rejected lower Integration-only approach because mocked exceptions can miss crash-specific handling. Rejected higher levels: Agentic/Workflow disqualified since no AI/ML decisions are involved.","test_description":"Run the pipeline with the real linter binary against a corpus containing one crash-triggering malformed file plus valid files; assert crash is captured, subsequent files are still linted, and final PR-comment payload is produced with partial results plus crash note.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.17,"System":0.81,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"Duplicate findings on the same line from overlapping rules are deduplicated in the output.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The failure arises when outputs from multiple rules are merged then rendered; this is cross-module orchestration (rule engine -> aggregation -> output), not only a single pure function in many implementations. Integration catches real key-construction/normalization mismatches that unit tests on dedup helper can miss. Integration brake check: (a) no real OS/network/subprocess required, (b) no AI/ML dependency, (c) no multi-agentic chain. Rejected higher levels: System disqualified by deterministic in-process data-flow behavior; Agentic/Workflow disqualified by no model involvement.","test_description":"Execute multiple overlapping rules on a fixture file so they emit same-line duplicates; pass through real aggregation/output pipeline; assert exactly one deduplicated finding per line/rule-equivalence key in final output.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.36,"Integration":0.59,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}}]}
